Author: whatever171
Text: Thank you so much <3  I always feel physically better when I eat, not as cold too, but it never outweighs the mental stress it gives me I’d become obsess with food and my body, and ignore everything else like my studies :\ so I’m definitely not on the road to recovery, but that’s okay because I don’t have it very badly and I’m comfortable with a 16-17 bmi :)

Author: LowStory
Text: Hey, I’m proud of you. I know—a lot of us here know—how hard hitting 1200 can be. You did great. Give yourself a hug from me!  Sidenote: Write down how you feel physically over the next 24 hours. Is your concentration better? Are you not as dizzy? That can be a good reminder when the guilt sets in.
